Date: 02 July 2026
Day 5 - Building Premium Food Cards
Today I learned:
Learned how CSS Positioning works using position: relative and position: absolute.
Understood why a parent needs position: relative before positioning child elements absolutely.
Added a "Best Seller" badge on food cards using absolute positioning.
Learned the difference between Margin (spacing) and Top/Left/Right/Bottom (positioning).
Fixed a CSS bug where every <span> was getting text-decoration: line-through by using a more specific selector (.card h4 span).
Learned about CSS Specificity and why more specific selectors override general ones.

Added Image Hover Zoom using:

transform: scale();
Learned why transform: scale() is preferred over increasing width for hover animations.

Understood the purpose of:

overflow: hidden;

to prevent zoomed images from overflowing outside the card.

Improved card interactions by using:
cursor: pointer
transition
transform
box-shadow

Learned how hovering a parent element can animate its child elements using selectors like:

.card:hover img
.card:hover .btn
Learned why gap is better than applying multiple margins when using Flexbox.
Understood how clean code organization makes CSS easier to maintain and debug.
Practiced thinking from a UI/UX perspective by discussing hover animations, user attention, and premium website interactions.

Keep Learning!! :)
